132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 172
H.P. 105 House of Representatives, January 14, 2025
An Act to Require the Maine State Police to Create a Statewide List
of Missing Persons
Reference to the Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative MILLIKEN of Blue Hill.
Cosponsored by Senator CYRWAY of Kennebec and
Representatives: ARDELL of Monticello, BABIN of Fort Fairfield, BISHOP of Bucksport,
DODGE of Belfast, GATTINE of Westbrook, LAJOIE of Lewiston, NUTTING of Oakland,
PERKINS of Dover-Foxcroft.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 25 MRSA §1512 is enacted to read:
3 §1512. Missing persons list
4 In cooperation with appropriate law enforcement agencies, the Bureau of State Police
5 shall establish and maintain a publicly accessible website that lists all open missing person
6 cases in the State. For each missing person listed, the website must contain a summary of
7 the details of the case, a picture of the missing person and the contact information for the
8 investigating agency.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This bill requires the Department of Public Safety, Bureau of State Police to establish
1111 and maintain a publicly accessible statewide missing persons list.
